76561198040954632,Recommended,477310,25367219,"Posted: 5 September, 2016",all,Generic Oonorio,"Pretty fun little game to play if you got a few quarters to spare. The difficulty curve get's pretty steep later on and the NG+ mode is a pretty broken but it's easy enough to beat with enough time and exploits. It's a little kaizo in the final levels so be ready for that. There's quite a few secret levels in it that are a little unsettling but nothing ""super spooky"" or anything.The game feels like the developer's first game so if you don't like that avoid it. Otherwise the game is pretty fun for it's price.Also it turns into a super deep avant-garde student art film later on and it's friggin' glorious."
